[]},{"name":"Gruffydd","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Welsh: The Welsh name; from creffydd, strong faith, or strong in faith. Gruffydd, a Welsh form of Gryffydd."],"variants":[]},{"name":"foel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, composed of two different Hebrew elements, <i>Yah(weh)</i> and <i>El</i>, both of which mean ‘God’ the implication of the name is that the Hebrew God, <i>Yahweh</i>, is the only true god. This is a common name in the Bible, being borne by, among others, one of King David's ‘mighty men’ (1 Chronicles 11:38), and a minor prophet who lived in the 8th century  bc . The name has been perennially popular as a Jewish name; it was also taken up by the Puritans and other Christian fundamentalists. The name has long been in regular use in North America but was uncommon in Britain until the 1990s. Well-known bearers of the name include the American singer and entertainer  Joel Grey  (  b. 1932 ), the West Indian cricketer  Joel Garner  (  b. 1952 ), and the American film director  Joel Coen  (  b. 1954 ). The French form  <b>Joël</b>  is also used in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gruffydd foel ap Gruffydd was born about 1250, in Cardiganshire, Wales, his father, Gruffydd ap Ivor, was 32 and his mother, Senana ferch Caradog, was 53. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Anne verch Robert. He died about 1289, in his hometown, at the age of 41."},"et":{"about 1250–about 1289":"umbes 1250–umbes 1289","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1244–Female":"1244–Surnud","1250–1289":"1250–1289","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1274–Female":"1274–Surnud","1279–1320":"1279–1320","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1198–1263":"1198–1263","about 1250":"umbes 1250","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","1274":"1274","1240":"1240","Abt 1279":"umbes 1279","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","